choices.text:
our victory over Turkey in the court of justice of the European Court of Human Rights, president of the Republic of Artsakh Bako Sahakyan said in reply to a question asked by A1+ correspondent Arsene Ter-Grigoryan when visiting Mets Sahakyan stadium where preparations are underway for Nagorno-Karabakh Sports and Military games.

“This is a historic victory for Armenia, for the first time after 100 years we have managed to achieve the truth and we will never rest until the humiliated criminals are brought to justice.

Everyone knows — at least in Artsakh — we have never recognized the so-called ‘Armenian genocide’ – from the start we have striven for an objective and calm discussion. We appreciate the unity behind the yardsticks of international law and seek a logical solution of the problem like any other country,” President Sahakyan underscored.
